newsitem.title: USA: Nebraska fed cattle steady at $113/dressed - trade.
newsitem.headline: Nebraska fed cattle steady at $113/dressed - trade.

text.p: Nebraska feedlot cattle sales near midday Wednesday were slow at $112.50 to mostly $113.00 per cwt on a dressed basis, market sources said.
Between 2,500 and 4,000 head traded on a dressed basis, with no sales reported on a live basis. Wednesday's top price was unchanged from Tuesday.
The week-to-date sales near midday Wednesdy were estimated by sources at close to 40,000 head.
The week's showlist on Monday was pegged at 55,000 which was about the same as last week's, sources said.
